<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>37-201.21</num>
  <heading>Sale of pro rata quantity.</heading>
  <text>Whenever any commodity is offered for sale at a stated price for a stated quantity, a smaller quantity shall be sold at a pro rata price unless the purchaser is informed to the contrary at the time of sale.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation type="History" doc="Stat. 66-3-ch118" path="§21">Mar. 3, 1921, 41 Stat. 1224, ch. 118, § 21</annotation>
